Robert Bates has been charged with second-degree manslaughter in the death of Eric Harris during a botched sting on April 2 . 
  A memo has revealed he was given special treatment when he was admitted into the Tulsa Sheriff's Office Deputy program . 
  He has been accused of shooting Harris dead instead of reaching for his Taser . 
  Documents suggest the department also violated training policies . 
  District Attorney has called for an investigation into the allegations . 
  Bates has pleaded not guilty to second- degree manslaughter . 
 